[1] Glomerella leaf spot - New York
Date: Fri 31 Aug 2012
Source: Cornell University Fruit News [edited]
http://blogs.cornell.edu/fruit/2012/08/31/glomerella-leaf-spot-a-new-disease-affecting-golden-delicious-apples-in-ny/


Glomerella leaf spot -- a new disease affecting Golden Delicious apples in NY?
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Golden Delicious trees in Hudson Valley Lab research orchard are yellowing and defoliating. Upon closer inspection, it may not be physiological leaf blotch (necrotic leaf blotch or Golden Delicious leaf blotch), but a fungal disease, glomerella leaf spot.

Look for dead spots on leaves with a concentric ring pattern. If you are seeing the symptoms you may want to consider an application of fungicide to slow it down, especially on late-maturing apple cultivars. Golden Delicious, Gala, Pink Lady, Goldrush, and Pristine cultivars are known to be susceptible. This disease can result in fruit rots, as well!

[Byline: Dave Rosenberger]

--
Communicated by:
